.TH "devm_kvasprintf" 9 "devm_kvasprintf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_kvasprintf \- Allocate resource managed space and format a string into that.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "char *" devm_kvasprintf
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ","
.BI "const char *fmt "  ","
.BI "va_list ap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Device to allocate memory for
.IP "gfp" 12
the GFP mask used in the \fBdevm_kmalloc\fP call when
allocating memory
.IP "fmt" 12
The \fBprintf\fP-style format string
.IP "ap" 12
Arguments for the format string
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to allocated string on success, NULL on failure.
